Description:
Total Perfection On 1/2 Acre
This stunning brick family home has been built with an obvious passion for quality & style and has been lovingly cared for by the current owners for over 14 years. The home boasts 3 spacious bedrooms, master with full ensuite and BIR & a well-appointed timber kitchen with stainless steel appliances that is positioned in the centre of the home and overlooks the meals area and has easy access to the separate family room and lounge. Special features include an open fire place, bar, split system heating and cooling and gas ducted heating. Outside you will find a useable and
meticulously maintained 1/2 acre allotment (approx.) that offers a sealed drive, double carport, single carport, established gardens, fantastic veggie patch, garden shed, man cave with toilet and a paved entertaining area that is the perfect place to sit back and enjoy the peaceful surrounds. From the moment you step inside you will feel at home, call today - your hills lifestyle awaits!

Description:
ECO RESORT ON 54 PRIVATE ACRES!
Designed by one of Melbourne's leading Environmentally Sustainable Design Consultants, this contemporary & unique home has the rigidity and strength normally reserved for commercial buildings & is located privately just minutes from Cockatoo & Emerald. The carefully outlined house oriented 30 degrees off true North towards East utilizes the sun for passive heating in winter and mid-season. In addition, the deviation towards East allows for early morning heat-up until late spring and from early autumn. The home features: 4 bedrooms (easily converted to 8 bedrooms), 2 bathrooms, 3 toilets, 2 x large open plan living areas, a designer kitchen, a huge Master Suite with gorgeous ensuite, parents retreat & magnificent views, a home office with reception area, a sensational 8 person indoor spa, an abundance of storage, a 60kl water tank for the house plus 30kl additional tank for garden, grid-connected solar power, 4 car carport, a magnificent outdoor entertaining area with outdoor kitchen & 54 natural acres giving you absolute privacy & your own window into nature. The home is a straw bale construction using recycled, local, low toxicity materials with the health of its occupants & the environment in mind, as well as offering the ultimate in energy efficiency. The primary form of heating is the double sided wood burning fireplace along with the house orientation to maximise the environmental impact & the home has double glazed windows to add to its exceptional insulation qualities. This magnificent property is beautifully finished & truly needs to be seen to be appreciated. We guarantee it will take your breath away.
CALL TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE INSPECTION TODAY!
For a more detailed overview of the features of the property please contact Grant Day on 0417 565 745 or 5968 6222

At the other end of the home is a generous 3rd bedroom with ensuite & open plan living area & kitchenette, ideal for the teenager, in-laws or potential dual occupancy. A great family package with heaps on space both inside and out.

Description:
Immerse Yourself in Quality & Style On 2 Acres
If you love to be surrounded by nature this is the property for you. With resident wombats, echidnas, kangaroos and an abundance of bird life together with the tranquil sound of the flowing creek on over 2 acres you can relax in your own private oasis.
Meander down the long driveway over the natural creek & discover this beautifully presented contemporary family home that offers a lifestyle of seclusion & luxury. Featuring double brick construction with timber lined ceilings and an abundance of windows to capture nature at its best.
The open floor plan & light filled design is embraced by a spectacular bush outlook from every window & provides comfortable accommodation for you & your family. Offering 3 bedrooms plus study (could easily be converted to the 4th bedroom), Solid timber country kitchen with large bench space and an abundance of cupboards, stainless steel appliances including 900mm Delonghi 6 burner gas cooktop, Delonghi double oven & miele dishwasher.
Other comfort features include gas & wood heating to ensure comfort throughout the cooler months and reverse cycle inverter air conditioner. This home has been renovated throughout with top of the range fittings, including high quality timber flooring, carpets, light fittings and new built in wood heater.
Fully tiled ensuite featuring stone accents and modern colour palette and a modern light filled bathroom will delight. Entertain in style around the salt chlorinated and solar heated pool or share a BBQ with friends in the paved undercover courtyard. Outside also offers a fully fenced paddock, currently home to the family goats, large chicken coop, garden shed, double carport and a planning permit for a 12 x 8 m colourbond triple garage. For those seeking both tranquillity & convenience, this one ticks all the boxes.

Better value will be hard to find!

Description:
Peace and Privacy On Over 1 Acre.
From the moment you set foot on this property you will feel instant relaxation and a sense of homeliness that this magnificent hills lifestyle property has to offer. This light filled home offers private views of the picturesque fern gully and a sense of space with the home featuring modern kitchen with stainless steel appliances, large adjoining dining room, separate lounge, 3 bedrooms, master offering a full ensuite. Special features include polished floorboards, reverse cycle heating/cooling and a fresh modern color scheme throughout. Outside offers decked entertaining area, veggie patch, garden shed, plenty of parking, walking tracks, fern gully and established gardens. Make this hills lifestyle yours today!
Cockatoo
Cockatoo is a town in Victoria, 48 km south-east of Melbourne's central business district. Its local government area is the Shire of Cardinia. Cockatoo is named after Cockatoo Creek, which runs through the town, and which the town was previously named.
Cockatoo's small commercial centre is located along a steep section of McBride Street and includes a small supermarket and a selection of cafes and other places to eat. The Puffing Billy tourist railway line crosses right next to the shops at the base of McBride Street, recreating those days of stream train travel from long ago as it regularly passes through the town centre.
Cockatoo has a good selection of sporting facilities. In the town centre along the west side of Pakenham Road is a bowling club, basketball courts, tennis courts and other recreational facilities. The Cockatoo Sports Complex is located in Mountain Road and consists of an indoor stadium, oval, athletics track and netball courts.
